  "translations": {
    "en": "Then look at your ruku and sujud, for the Prophet prayed the most complete prayers, though in practice it was least burdensome. Know that all your affairs follow your prayers – whoever is negligent of his prayers will be more negligent in other acts of worship. I beseech Him Who sees and cannot be seen, and He is on the highest horizon, that He may take us and you among those He loves and is pleased with, so that He may help us remember and praise Him, worship Him best, fulfil His covenant, and in all that He determines in our affairs here and hereafter.",
    "ur": "Then look at your ruku and sujud, for the Prophet prayed the most complete prayers, though in practice it was least burdensome. Know that all your affairs follow your prayers – whoever is negligent of his prayers will be more negligent in other acts of worship. I beseech Him Who sees and cannot be seen, and He is on the highest horizon, that He may take us and you among those He loves and is pleased with, so that He may help us remember and praise Him, worship Him best, fulfil His covenant, and in all that He determines in our affairs here and hereafter.",
